title: Status app crashes with some golang errors

body: from logs, it doesn't seem related to a browser tab, it's a panic in go, but we don't interact with go in browser tab somehow

> from logs, it doesn't seem related to a browser tab, it's a panic in go, but we don't interact with go in browser tab somehow

thanks Andrey, i am still not clear on the steps, so just added the ones i did
Can't reproduce on LG V20 (Android 8) - tried ~5 times, waited om browser tab ~3 min.
@adambabik since it is go related (assuming i am reading logs correctly) - could you please take a look?
@mandrigin could you take a look, please?
Quite interesting. It seems like a bug in github.com/golang/snappy (compression lib) or github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum rlpx implementation. Are we able to reproduce it? @asemiankevich

> Quite interesting. It seems like a bug in github.com/golang/snappy (compression lib) or github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum rlpx implementation. Are we able to reproduce it? @asemiankevich

just reproduced it in release candidate 0.9.12 build 13 (android) but without any steps , just opened status and stayed in home screen @adambabik

also, reproduced when staying with camera opened (to scan qr code)
